1
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:17,280
Someone's dead! Someone's dead!

2
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:01,000
What you're saying is

3
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:04,280
the suspect's targets aren't random

4
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:06,200
The targets may be random,

5
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,840
but abduction sites are chosen in advance.

6
00:01:14,439 --> 00:01:15,840
The two rape cases at the precinct,

7
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,879
the victims also left entertainment venues

8
00:01:17,879 --> 00:01:19,280
by taxi.

9
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,840
Could it be the same perpetrator?

10
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:22,599
Deviant rapists are typically obsessive,

11
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,680
showing patterns of repetition

12
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,560
and ritualistic behavior.

13
00:01:26,599 --> 00:01:28,079
And as the crimes accumulate,

14
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,879
the psychological need intensifies,

15
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,640
violence escalates,

16
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,400
and methods grow more brutal.

17
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:34,680
But this case

18
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,280
differs fundamentally from the precinct's.

19
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:38,439
Suspects don't usually make

20
00:01:38,439 --> 00:01:39,599
drastic changes to their methods.

21
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,400
For example,

22
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,280
suddenly carving characters.

23
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,319
There's another possibility:

24
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:50,719
the suspect deliberately altered his methods

25
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,480
to throw us off the trail.

26
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:55,159
It's possible,

27
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,519
but highly unlikely.

28
00:01:57,439 --> 00:01:59,359
Unless he's under extreme pressure,

29
00:01:59,719 --> 00:02:01,680
or carrying out some kind of mission.

30
00:02:02,719 --> 00:02:03,680
Or perhaps

31
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,680
he's copying a more complex crime pattern.

32
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,400
Either way,

33
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:10,759
we need to catch the suspect quickly

34
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,840
to prevent more innocent victims.

35
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:14,759
Qingming.

36
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,439
The Major Crimes Unit has been short-handed.

37
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,919
We transferred a new guy from the station.

38
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:18,680
Jiang Han.

39
00:02:20,159 --> 00:02:20,800
Captain Zhao.

40
00:02:21,039 --> 00:02:21,800
Supervisors

41
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,639
and colleagues,

42
00:02:22,919 --> 00:02:23,599
I'm new here,

43
00:02:23,719 --> 00:02:24,719
I look forward to working with you.

44
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,479
Bro,

45
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,400
your analysis just now was spot on.

46
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:29,280
You're like

47
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,000
a master detective in criminal psychology!

48
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:31,879
You two know each other?

49
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,080
As they say, no fight, no friendship.

50
00:02:35,199 --> 00:02:36,159
Felt like old friends right away.

51
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,719
Li Kaiyang, Deputy Captain of Major Crimes.

52
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:39,919
From now on, you'll be following him.

53
00:02:41,479 --> 00:02:42,680
Chief Xing, this guy...

54
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,240
Mentor, I'll go wherever you point me.

55
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:44,919
Kaiyang,

56
00:02:45,159 --> 00:02:47,120
Jiang Han majored in crime investigation.

57
00:02:47,599 --> 00:02:48,599
He can be a great help to you.

58
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:53,759
One month. If you can't learn to investigate

59
00:02:53,879 --> 00:02:54,840
and only focus on plucking your eyebrows,

60
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,159
go back to where you came from.

61
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,719
I trimmed a few eyebrow hairs

62
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:01,599
and you can even tell?

63
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,039
The character the killer carved is ancient Chinese.

64
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,520
Very few people use it now.

65
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:07,879
In the Kangxi Dictionary,

66
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,319
this character means the same as "miao."

67
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,240
In northern dialects,

68
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,960
it stands for beauty or a beautiful woman.

69
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,360
But in southern dialects,

70
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:17,840
it means a brothel keeper or a prostitute.

71
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,560
Chief Xing.

72
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,159
The suspect in this kidnap and rape case

73
00:03:24,159 --> 00:03:25,840
also wore red gloves during the crime.

74
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:28,680
Very similar to the 531 case 22 years ago.

75
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,120
Plus the identical carved character.

76
00:03:31,439 --> 00:03:32,000
Do you think

77
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,120
these two cases could possibly be linked?

78
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,840
Linking cases is no small matter.

79
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:40,599
To reopen a case closed 22 years ago,

80
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,159
we need sufficient grounds.

81
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:43,639
After all,

82
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,840
the 531 case was too unique.

83
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,879
It involved too many families.

84
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,439
The 531 case from 22 years ago...

85
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:53,919
Isn't this exactly...

86
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:54,719
Chief Xing, Captain Zhao.

87
00:03:54,879 --> 00:03:56,520
A naked female body was found at Liuye Lake.

88
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:00,280
We'll discuss linking the cases

89
00:04:00,439 --> 00:04:01,240
at another time.

90
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:02,360
Qingming.

91
00:04:03,039 --> 00:04:03,960
You handle the rape case.

92
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:05,319
Li Kaiyang.

93
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,360
You take charge of the murder case.

94
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:06,800
Yes, sir.

95
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,639
Yes, sir.

96
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,520
Fang Ping, Lin Xue.

97
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,520
You stay and help Wang organize files.

98
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,000
Why?

99
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:16,040
You're not ready yet.

100
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,720
I want to go to the murder scene.

101
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:18,759
You can go,

102
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:20,160
but someone else will take you.

103
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,399
Wait, no...

104
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,160
Li Kaiyang

105
00:04:25,519 --> 00:04:26,759
is cold on the outside but warm inside.

106
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:28,319
But he's got a knack for investigation.

107
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:31,079
Don't rush. Learn from him.

108
00:04:31,319 --> 00:04:32,000
Take your time getting to know him.

109
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,680
Chief Xing.

110
00:04:34,759 --> 00:04:35,360
Here you go.

111
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:40,600
Wait...

112
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,079
Captain Li.

113
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,360
Captain Li.

114
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:56,079
The forensic examiner's almost here.

115
00:04:56,319 --> 00:04:57,639
Don't overstep your role.

116
00:04:58,079 --> 00:04:58,680
Brother Wang,

117
00:04:59,079 --> 00:05:01,600
Captain Li's skills aren't quite on par

118
00:05:04,319 --> 00:05:05,439
with a forensic examiner's.

119
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,399
Didn't know Sister Fei trained in martial arts.

120
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,600
You do this every time.

121
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,040
You can't read the room at all.

122
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,120
I was complimenting her!

123
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,600
She's angry again.

124
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,720
Mom, it's me, Xinxin.

125
00:05:33,439 --> 00:05:34,319
Mom.

126
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,040
Mom.

127
00:05:37,399 --> 00:05:38,079
Xinxin.

128
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:38,920
Come here.

129
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,839
Mom.

130
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,879
Mom, I want my mom!

131
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,639
Xiangxiang.

132
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:49,560
Mom, wake up! Mom!

133
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,519
Xiangxiang, is that you?

134
00:05:51,079 --> 00:05:51,720
Xiangxiang.

135
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,560
Xiangxiang, is that you? Xiangxiang!

136
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:56,480
Xiangxiang, you can't leave me!

137
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,240
Xiangxiang!

138
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:00,560
It's you! Give me back my mom!

139
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:05,000
Xinxin.

140
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,720
What do you mean?

141
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:10,279
You killed my mom!

142
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:12,519
Talk!

143
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,319
You got some boy toy on the side?

144
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:18,879
Honey, you've got it wrong.

145
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,240
I don't buy it.

146
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:22,759
What's going on?

147
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,680
Making more money than me now, huh?

148
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,680
Think you're a big shot now!

149
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:28,000
Honey, you're drunk.

150
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,040
Let me wash your feet.

151
00:06:29,399 --> 00:06:30,319
Then we'll go to bed.

152
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:32,800
Wash my feet, wash my feet, I'll wash them.

153
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,240
Come on, wash my feet.

154
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:35,240
Wash my feet.

155
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,879
Honey, don't hit me.

156
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,959
Our child is home.

157
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,959
Our child is home. Stop hitting me!

158
00:06:40,439 --> 00:06:41,399
Xinxin is home.

159
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,759
I'm begging you.

160
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:44,759
The child.

161
00:06:44,759 --> 00:06:45,279
Come here.

162
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:46,120
The child is home.

163
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:47,240
Let me tell you something.

164
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,160
If I ever find out

165
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:52,040
you're cheating on me,

166
00:06:52,839 --> 00:06:54,000
I'll kill you.

167
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:55,680
I'll kill you!

168
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,279
Please, don't hit me.

169
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,000
Xiangxiang's death has nothing to do with me.

170
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,079
She was my wife.

171
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:17,240
How could I possibly kill my own wife?

172
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,959
So you're saying the child is lying?

173
00:07:20,639 --> 00:07:22,560
Kids don't understand grown-up games.

174
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,639
From the 17th to the 21st,

175
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:25,959
what were you doing?

176
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:26,800
I already told you.

177
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,399
Then tell me again.

178
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,759
The 17th was a Sunday.

179
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:33,600
Around 5, I dropped my kid off at school,

180
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:34,879
then I went home.

181
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,439
Oh, I, I, I...

182
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,120
My daughter goes to a boarding school.

183
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:40,000
What about Liu Xiang?

184
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,480
She didn't come home.

185
00:07:43,759 --> 00:07:45,120
Her workplace is busiest on weekends.

186
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,360
When did you last see Liu Xiang?

187
00:07:48,839 --> 00:07:50,319
The afternoon of the 18th, I think.

188
00:07:52,079 --> 00:07:53,360
I went to see her at her workplace.

189
00:07:54,519 --> 00:07:56,560
She had training in Shanghai on the 19th.

190
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,519
An early morning bullet train.

191
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,720
She was worried about missing it,

192
00:08:00,399 --> 00:08:01,639
so she stayed at the company dorm.

193
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,600
So I went back home to mind the shop.

194
00:08:05,759 --> 00:08:06,839
Didn't go out after that.

195
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,040
Notice anything?

196
00:08:09,879 --> 00:08:10,759
Feng Bing's speech,

197
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:12,079
micro-expressions,

198
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,279
body language,

199
00:08:13,439 --> 00:08:14,720
showed almost no flaws.

200
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:17,879
What do you think?

201
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,920
I disagree.

202
00:08:20,519 --> 00:08:21,680
I think he's lying.

203
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:24,040
Look at his expression.

204
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,879
He's clearly hiding his fear and panic.

205
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,480
Your wife was missing for days,

206
00:08:30,399 --> 00:08:31,279
and you didn't report it?

207
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,440
Her business trips always take about a week.

208
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,600
But I really never imagined...

209
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:40,960
I never imagined this.

210
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:41,679
Look.

211
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,919
When he was describing all of this,

212
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,039
he was way too fluent.

213
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:47,840
What you said

214
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,080
does make some sense.

215
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:52,399
Seems when you're not throwing fists,

216
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,960
your IQ actually comes back a bit.

217
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,039
Brother Wang.

218
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,759
Head over to Liren Medical Aesthetics right now.

219
00:08:58,960 --> 00:08:59,919
Get Jiang Han to assist you.

220
00:09:00,559 --> 00:09:01,159
Just wait.

221
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:02,440
I'll definitely

222
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,279
find proof that this guy's a killer.

223
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,080
Thanks, mentor.

224
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,200
Victim is female.

225
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,600
Age between 28 and 33.

226
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:27,279
Based on body temperature, rigor mortis,

227
00:09:27,279 --> 00:09:28,399
and the formation of livor mortis,

228
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,519
time of death is within the past 24 hours.

229
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,519
No froth in the mouth or nasal cavity.

230
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,000
Drowning has been preliminarily ruled out.

231
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,399
Multiple fractures to the sternum and ribs.

232
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:40,759
The spine is damaged.

233
00:09:40,879 --> 00:09:41,759
Looks like impact injuries.

234
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:09,960
You're saying

235
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,879
Liu Xiang never went to Shanghai at all?

236
00:10:12,879 --> 00:10:14,200
The morning we were supposed to leave

237
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,919
Hello, Liren Medical Beauty.

238
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,240
Hello, hello.

239
00:10:20,799 --> 00:10:22,399
Liu Xiang suddenly felt unwell this morning.

240
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:24,320
She said she wouldn't leave with us.

241
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,399
Once she felt better,

242
00:10:25,399 --> 00:10:26,919
she'd take a later train to Shanghai herself.

243
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:28,600
Unwell? Was it serious?

244
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,320
You really guessed it.

245
00:10:33,679 --> 00:10:35,159
That guy was putting on an act.

246
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,039
On the afternoon of the 18th,

247
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,440
did Feng Bing come here?

248
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,000
That day, Sister Liu Xiang

249
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:44,960
was chosen as our store's image ambassador.

250
00:10:45,159 --> 00:10:46,159
She was taking photos here.

251
00:10:46,919 --> 00:10:48,879
Her husband kept watching from the door.

252
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,519
He stood there with a grim face.

253
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:51,480
It was pretty scary.

254
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:52,919
I called him in,

255
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:53,799
but he wouldn't come in.

256
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:55,440
Hey, aren't you Sister Xiang's husband?

257
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,320
After a few minutes,

258
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,159
Liu Xiang's husband left.

259
00:10:59,879 --> 00:11:00,559
And then?

260
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,279
Then Liu Xiang hurried off work.

261
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,600
You mean Feng Bing didn't pick her up?

262
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,240
I thought it was strange too.

263
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,519
Are you sure she didn't come back to the dorm?

264
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,440
I'm sure.

265
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,200
Fixing a car, boss?

266
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:23,240
Major Crimes Unit.

267
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,000
Hello.

268
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:28,720
This car,

269
00:11:29,279 --> 00:11:30,360
was it repaired here?

270
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:31,639
That's right.

271
00:11:32,039 --> 00:11:32,960
Well,

272
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,000
the front bumper was replaced.

273
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,039
The hood had bodywork and a paint job.

274
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,799
When was the car brought in?

275
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,480
Around 7 p.m. on the 18th.

276
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,960
I found blood inside the front bumper.

277
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,559
He said he ran over a dog.

278
00:11:48,879 --> 00:11:50,320
If Feng Bing wanted to pick her up,

279
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,120
it had to be in this parking lot.

280
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,240
Chairman Xu, you're here.

281
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,039
Mm.

282
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,159
Have the police arrived?

283
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,840
Yes, they're still here.

284
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,919
Officers,

285
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:08,240
you're here about Dr. Liu's case?

286
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:09,879
Chairman Xu,

287
00:12:10,159 --> 00:12:11,159
I've heard so much about you.

288
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,759
Finally meeting you in person.

289
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,440
You flatter me.

290
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,720
I'm Wang Yonglin

291
00:12:15,919 --> 00:12:16,639
from Major Crimes.

292
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:18,159
This is my colleague, Jiang Han.

293
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:20,559
Regarding Liu Xiang's death,

294
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:22,440
I have new information to share.

295
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:26,200
About six months ago,

296
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,039
when she was giving me a beauty injection,

297
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,360
I accidentally noticed bruises on her.

298
00:12:32,559 --> 00:12:34,279
After I pressed her repeatedly,

299
00:12:34,519 --> 00:12:35,559
she finally revealed

300
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,559
that she'd been abused at home for years.

301
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,960
That Feng Bing really is a piece of trash.

302
00:12:41,519 --> 00:12:42,360
Officers,

303
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,519
in my heart,

304
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:46,240
every employee is like family to me.

305
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,799
I don't want any of them to be hurt.

306
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:51,799
Please catch the killer quickly

307
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,240
and bring justice to the victim.

308
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,759
Rest assured.

309
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,600
That's our duty.

310
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,480
You're welcome.

311
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,600
What we can confirm now is

312
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,720
that Liu Xiang suffered domestic violence.

313
00:13:10,799 --> 00:13:12,559
He didn't actually hit someone, did he?

314
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:13,919
Where's the old front bumper?

315
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,360
Over there.

316
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,399
We haven't had time to dispose of it yet.

317
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:34,120
Mentor, on the 18th at 5:46 PM,

318
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,519
Feng Bing was the one who picked her up.

319
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,559
I'll send you the photo.

320
00:13:36,639 --> 00:13:37,279
Okay.

321
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:23,240
Ma'am!

322
00:14:23,679 --> 00:14:24,639
Are you okay, ma'am?

323
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:25,799
Young lady!

324
00:14:36,559 --> 00:14:37,000
Hey!

325
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,000
Who's there?

326
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:38,799
What are you doing?

327
00:14:39,679 --> 00:14:40,159
Hey!

328
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,039
How's it going?

329
00:14:50,679 --> 00:14:51,399
Any breakthroughs?

330
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,480
We found the time of the incident

331
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:56,919
and proof Feng Bing picked up Liu Xiang.

332
00:14:58,960 --> 00:14:59,759
How about on your end?

333
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:03,600
We checked most downtown nightlife spots.

334
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:05,639
No useful leads so far.

335
00:15:09,919 --> 00:15:10,759
What did you say?

336
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,240
You didn't pick up Liu Xiang on the 18th?

337
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:14,919
No, I didn't.

338
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:18,399
I went straight home from her workplace.

339
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:21,000
If you didn't take her home,

340
00:15:21,279 --> 00:15:23,159
then why, before she left for Shanghai,

341
00:15:23,159 --> 00:15:24,279
did you call to request leave for her?

342
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:25,320
Talk!

343
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,279
A phone call?

344
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:31,200
What... what phone call?

345
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,639
I have no idea what you're talking about.

346
00:15:40,279 --> 00:15:41,039
Feng Bing.

347
00:15:41,799 --> 00:15:42,840
Open your eyes wide.

348
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,679
Take a good look.

349
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,519
Honey, have some chocolate.

350
00:16:06,519 --> 00:16:07,039
It's really good.

351
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,759
One photo

352
00:16:14,919 --> 00:16:16,320
proves I killed someone?

353
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,440
Captain Zhao, Captain Li.

354
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,639
The red glove appeared again.

355
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:24,559
Stay calm.

356
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,080
Keep interrogating him.

357
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,759
Try to crack him soon.

358
00:16:28,399 --> 00:16:29,159
Leave the scene to me.

359
00:16:37,679 --> 00:16:39,000
I'll say it again.

360
00:16:40,639 --> 00:16:41,919
I didn't pick her up that day.

361
00:16:43,159 --> 00:16:44,840
These look like marks from hands

362
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:45,720
pressing down on the neck.

363
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,120
She got in, said a few words, then left.

364
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:50,120
I don't know what she did after that.

365
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,600
The body was submerged for so long,

366
00:16:53,799 --> 00:16:54,919
plus the rain washing over it,

367
00:16:55,519 --> 00:16:56,720
trace evidence is hard to preserve.

368
00:17:03,879 --> 00:17:05,279
Anyway, I didn't kill her.

369
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:10,359
I don't know who did.

370
00:17:24,279 --> 00:17:25,400
Then what about these scratches?

371
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:28,480
Look up at me.

372
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:34,400
Did you strangle Liu Xiang,

373
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,480
and she scratched you fighting back?

374
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:37,240
Talk!

375
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,759
No, no.

376
00:17:39,119 --> 00:17:40,559
This... my cat scratched me.

377
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:42,440
I... I really didn't kill anyone.

378
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:43,160
I really didn't kill anyone.

379
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:43,920
Stop pushing me, okay?

380
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:44,759
I really didn't kill anyone.

381
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:47,200
Captain Li.

382
00:17:47,599 --> 00:17:48,400
Forensic Sun said

383
00:17:48,599 --> 00:17:50,640
the report on the victim's samples is in.

384
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,240
Bring it over right away.

385
00:17:54,759 --> 00:17:55,240
Yes, sir.

386
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:57,240
Feng Bing.

387
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,759
It's not too late to confess.

388
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,599
Feng Bing.

389
00:18:07,559 --> 00:18:09,119
Your daughter is only eight.

390
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,880
She'll never see her mother again.

391
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,480
Xiangxiang did nothing wrong.

392
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:20,880
It was all my fault.

393
00:18:24,039 --> 00:18:25,640
I'm the one who strangled Liu Xiang.

394
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,160
I strangled Liu Xiang.
